BRIEFLY 
Maxwell Buys Into Leading Hungarian Daily: Media magnate Robert Maxwell bought 
40% of a top Hungarian newspaper. 
Maxwell Communication Corp. paid between $1.7 million and $3.4 million for 40% 
of Magyar Hirlap, Maxwell told reporters. The daily has a circulation of about 
100,000. The other partners in a new joint company called Magyar Hirlap 
Publishing include a Hungarian banking consortium with 40%, the Magyar Hirlap 
Foundation with 5% and Pallas Publishers with 14%. 
